pi-stomp (3.2.0-7~pre1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Prerelease from the prerelease-for-v2 branch — pi-Stomp v2 hardware
    support plus the UI performance work.

  [ v2 hardware ]
  * Derive the real SPI clock from the SoC instead of assuming a Pi 4/5:
    spi_timing now reads /proc/device-tree/compatible and models each
    controller's divisor rounding, so the Pi 3 (v2) gets correct transfer-time
    estimates rather than the Pi 5's. Drives the LCD inline-push gate, the
    emulator, and lcd320x240's poll_divisor.
  * Parameterdialog now edits parameters on the same quantized step grid as
    the v3 tweak encoders (common/parameter_steps.py), so one detent of the
    nav encoder — the only encoder on v2 — moves a value by the same amount.
  * Skip the aggressive LCD reset path on v2; it is no longer needed.

  [ Performance ]
  * Rewrite the pedalboard render loop: cached glyphs/tints, fewer full
    repaints, and cheaper text and panel painting.
  * WebSocket send loop parks on a wakeup event instead of a 1 ms poll, and
    the send/receive tasks now race FIRST_COMPLETED so a closed socket is
    noticed immediately and reconnects cleanly.
  * Run the dpkg version check on a background thread (modalapi/version_check)
    so it no longer stalls startup or the UI.
  * Coalesce MIDI/control updates with max_drain=1, matching pistomptre.

  [ Analog inputs ]
  * Detect a disconnected/floating ADC pin (e.g. an expression-pedal jack with
    nothing plugged in) and suppress the 60 Hz mains-hum noise it aliases into
    the poll stream, sleeping the input until a real pedal wakes it.

  [ WiFi ]
  * Support WPA3 networks.
  * Optimistic WiFi menu: acts on the selection immediately instead of waiting
    for NetworkManager to settle.
  * Fix stale scan results lingering in the network list.
  * Simplify the WiFi command/ops layer.

 -- Cam Gorrie <sastraxi@gmail.com>  Sat, 11 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0400

